task.summary: Automatic code cleanup, removed eclipse files

Update GroupManagerImpl -Managed all commands except GroupCommands.SYNC -Reduced ACK usage (channels are reliable, so they're only needed for synchronization among processes [like resume execution after JOINING])
Update GroupManagerImpl -Made JOINING behaviour more robust
Update GroupManagerImpl, MessagingMiddleware, MessagingMiddlewareImpl Activated a local lock in MessagingMiddleware that enables to stop all (active) operations while a new replica is joining
Update VectorClocks, VectorClocksTest -simplified VectorClocks.update -Fixed VectorClocksTest with new constructor -Added a couple test cases

HUGE DEBUG IN GROUP COMMUNICATION -Added support for usage of different ports, both ad applicative and middleware level --Made GroupManager be created with Socket instead String (hostname) --Made MessagingMiddleware be created with Socket instead String (hostname) -Divided Main.main into sub-functions for maintainability -Made PrimitiveParser work with ObjectStreams instead of custom interfaces --Deleted NetworkReader.java and NetworkWriter.java --Deleted PrimitiveParserRunnable.writeObjectSafe, readObjectSafe -NodeInfo tracks streams also, not only socket --2 setters for socket, the one with a boolean arg can initialize the streams --Update LeaderGroupManager, OrdinaryGroupManager so to use the correct setters (if the streams has already been created, they shouldn't be created again)
Update VectorClock: renamed, simplified VectorClock.compareTo, added VectorClock.canAccept
Update NodeInfo, NodeInfoTest: smarter OO programming Updated to adapt: - LeaderGroupManager - OrdinaryGroupManager
Update LeaderGroupManagerTest: fixed after updates to NodeInfo
Update Main, OrdinaryGroupManager: handled protocol exceptions

Update MessagingMiddleware, GroupManager, GroupManagerFactory: simplified synchronization -Synch by MessagingMiddleware methods -MessagingMiddleware passed in GroupManager construction
